        "1. **Why the Acceptable Names work**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Grade_test,\n",
        "  Covid_19_cases,\n",
        "  Sale_price_2021,\n",
        "  miva_learners:  \n",
        "      **These use underscores (_) instead of spaces to separate words, which is perfectly valid and standard in python.**\n",
        "\n",
        "- term2: This is valid because it starts with a letter. Numbers are        allowed as long as they aren't the very first character.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Why the Unacceptable Names Fail**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Test(grade): Unacceptable because it uses parentheses (). In Python, parentheses are reserved for calling functions, not naming variables.\n",
        "\n",
        "- covid-19-cases: Unacceptable because it uses hyphens (-). Pythonreads a hyphen as a minus sign, so it tries to subtract 19 from covid.\n",
        "\n",
        "- 2 term: Unacceptable because it starts with a number and contains a space.\n",
        "\n",
        "- 2021sales_price: Unacceptable because it starts with a number.\n",
        "\n",
        "- miva&learners: Unacceptable because it contains the special character &, which Python doesn't allow the variable names.\n",
